{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"dnV+BuwqyEfw+UusJiTx++MD/TQ=","kind":"plan","title":"Slice 4 — Body Divergence: Visibility \u0026 Recovery Implementation Plan"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"01sz3ZVowM0fRCPurIxihxZFRz4=","body":"# Slice 4 — Body Divergence: Visibility \u0026 Recovery Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Make an entry's edit history visible and recoverable — `kref log \u003cid\u003e` (operation timeline), `kref diff \u003cid\u003e` (every body version), and a coarse `◆ merged` flag — so a concurrently-edited body is never silently lost.\n\n**Architecture:** Read-only, over stable public git-bug APIs. `entry.Entry` embeds `*dag.Entity`, so `Operations()` yields every op (including both branches' `SetBody`s after a sync-merge) in Lamport order; we map them to render-friendly structs. The `◆ merged` signal comes from the commit graph (`repo.ListCommits` + `ReadCommit().Parents` — a merge commit means concurrent editing happened). No op→commit mapping, no git-bug internals.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go 1.26.4, cobra, ginkgo/gomega, git-bug `entity/dag` + `repository`. No new dependencies.\n\n**Spec:** `docs/dev/specs/2026-06-20-unified-entry-model-design.md` §4.1 (body divergence), scoped per the slice-4 decision to **visibility \u0026 recovery** (precise op-level concurrency detection + auto-reconcile were deferred as they require git-bug-internal op-pack parsing; keep-both already guarantees nothing is lost, and `log`/`diff` guarantee nothing is silent).\n\n## Why this scope\n\n`Operations()` returns a flat, totally-ordered list — git-bug exposes no operation DAG topology publicly, and Lamport clocks are a total order, so precise \"these two are concurrent\" labeling isn't cleanly available. But after a sync-merge, `Operations()` still contains **both** branches' `SetBody` ops, so `kref log`/`kref diff` surface every version (the \"clobbered\" one included) with author + time — delivering see-and-recover. The commit graph gives a coarse but honest \"this entry was merged\" flag. `reconcile` is just `kref edit` after looking (the next edit linearizes the DAG anyway).\n\n## File Structure\n\n- **Create** `internal/entry/history.go` — `LogEntry`, `BodyVersion`, `(*Entry).Log()`, `(*Entry).BodyVersions()`.\n- **Create** `internal/entry/history_test.go` — unit tests.\n- **Modify** `internal/entry/snapshot.go` — `Merged bool` field (set by the store layer, like `Tier`).\n- **Modify** `internal/store/store.go` — `Log`, `BodyVersions`, `Merged` methods.\n- **Modify** `internal/store/store_test.go` — store tests incl. a real sync-merge integration test for `Merged`.\n- **Modify** `internal/render/render.go` — `Log`, `BodyVersions` renderers; `◆ merged` marker in `Show`/`List`.\n- **Modify** `internal/render/render_test.go` — render tests.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/commands.go` — `newLogCmd`, `newDiffCmd`; set `snap.Merged` in `show`/`list`.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/main.go` — register `log`, `diff`.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` — CLI specs.\n- **Modify** `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`.\n\nSequencing: entry history (T1) → store methods (T2) → render (T3) → log/diff commands (T4) → merged flag (T5) → docs/verify (T6).\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: `entry.Entry.Log()` + `BodyVersions()`\n\n**Files:** `internal/entry/history.go` (new), `internal/entry/history_test.go` (new)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing tests**\n\n`internal/entry/history_test.go`:\n\n```go\npackage entry_test\n\nimport (\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Entry.Log\", func() {\n\tIt(\"maps each operation to a typed log entry in order\", func() {\n\t\tauthor := newAuthor(newTestRepo())\n\t\te := entry.New(entry.TierShared)\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewCreate(author, \"spec\", \"Title\"))\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewSetBody(author, \"v1 body\"))\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewSetStatus(author, \"accepted\"))\n\t\tlog := e.Log()\n\t\tExpect(log).To(HaveLen(3))\n\t\tExpect(log[0].Op).To(Equal(\"create\"))\n\t\tExpect(log[1].Op).To(Equal(\"set-body\"))\n\t\tExpect(log[2].Op).To(Equal(\"set-status\"))\n\t\tExpect(log[2].Detail).To(Equal(\"accepted\"))\n\t})\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Entry.BodyVersions\", func() {\n\tIt(\"returns each SetBody body in order\", func() {\n\t\tauthor := newAuthor(newTestRepo())\n\t\te := entry.New(entry.TierShared)\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewCreate(author, \"spec\", \"T\"))\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewSetBody(author, \"first\"))\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewSetBody(author, \"second\"))\n\t\tvs := e.BodyVersions()\n\t\tExpect(vs).To(HaveLen(2))\n\t\tExpect(vs[0].Body).To(Equal(\"first\"))\n\t\tExpect(vs[1].Body).To(Equal(\"second\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n\u003e `entry.New(tier)` and the op constructors are already public; `newAuthor(newTestRepo())` is the existing test helper. `Append` is from the embedded `*dag.Entity`. The ops are visible to `Operations()` immediately (they sit in staging) — confirm in Step 3; `Operations()` returns `append(e.ops, e.staging...)`, so staged ops are included.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -6`\nExpected: FAIL — `e.Log undefined` / `e.BodyVersions undefined`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement**\n\n`internal/entry/history.go`:\n\n```go\npackage entry\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"time\"\n)\n\n// LogEntry is a render-friendly view of one operation in an entry's history.\ntype LogEntry struct {\n\tOp     string    // create | set-body | set-title | set-status | add-label | remove-label | add-link | remove-link | tombstone | restore | origin\n\tAuthor string\n\tTime   time.Time\n\tDetail string // op-specific one-line summary\n}\n\n// Log maps the entry's operations (in Lamport order) to typed log entries.\n// After a sync-merge this includes every branch's operations, so a\n// concurrently-edited body is visible rather than silently shadowed.\nfunc (e *Entry) Log() []LogEntry {\n\tops := e.Operations()\n\tout := make([]LogEntry, 0, len(ops))\n\tfor _, op := range ops {\n\t\tle := LogEntry{Author: op.Author().Name(), Time: op.Time()}\n\t\tswitch o := op.(type) {\n\t\tcase *Create:\n\t\t\tle.Op, le.Detail = \"create\", fmt.Sprintf(\"%s %q\", o.Kind, o.Title)\n\t\tcase *SetBody:\n\t\t\tle.Op, le.Detail = \"set-body\", fmt.Sprintf(\"%d chars\", len(o.Body))\n\t\tcase *SetTitle:\n\t\t\tle.Op, le.Detail = \"set-title\", o.Title\n\t\tcase *SetStatus:\n\t\t\tle.Op, le.Detail = \"set-status\", o.Status\n\t\tcase *AddLabel:\n\t\t\tle.Op, le.Detail = \"add-label\", o.Label\n\t\tcase *RemoveLabel:\n\t\t\tle.Op, le.Detail = \"remove-label\", o.Label\n\t\tcase *AddLink:\n\t\t\tle.Op, le.Detail = \"add-link\", o.LinkType+\" \"+o.To\n\t\tcase *RemoveLink:\n\t\t\tle.Op, le.Detail = \"remove-link\", o.To\n\t\tcase *Tombstone:\n\t\t\tle.Op = \"tombstone\"\n\t\tcase *Restore:\n\t\t\tle.Op = \"restore\"\n\t\tcase *RecordOrigin:\n\t\t\tle.Op, le.Detail = \"origin\", o.Trigger+\" by \"+o.Actor\n\t\tdefault:\n\t\t\tle.Op = \"op\"\n\t\t}\n\t\tout = append(out, le)\n\t}\n\treturn out\n}\n\n// BodyVersion is one historical body, captured from a SetBody operation.\ntype BodyVersion struct {\n\tAuthor string\n\tTime   time.Time\n\tBody   string\n}\n\n// BodyVersions returns each SetBody body in order — the material for `kref diff`\n// and for recovering a body that a later edit superseded.\nfunc (e *Entry) BodyVersions() []BodyVersion {\n\tvar out []BodyVersion\n\tfor _, op := range e.Operations() {\n\t\tif sb, ok := op.(*SetBody); ok {\n\t\t\tout = append(out, BodyVersion{Author: op.Author().Name(), Time: op.Time(), Body: sb.Body})\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn out\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run the tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: PASS. Run `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go vet ./internal/entry/`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: gofmt + commit**\n\n```bash\ngofmt -w internal/entry/history.go internal/entry/history_test.go\ngit add internal/entry/history.go internal/entry/history_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(entry): Log() and BodyVersions() over the operation history\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: `store.Log`, `BodyVersions`, `Merged`\n\n**Files:** `internal/store/store.go`, `internal/store/store_test.go`, `internal/entry/snapshot.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add the `Merged` field to the snapshot**\n\nIn `internal/entry/snapshot.go`, add to the `Snapshot` struct after `Provenance`:\n\n```go\n\tMerged         bool          `json:\"merged\"` // set by the store from the commit graph; not from Compile\n```\n\nThen run `gofmt -w internal/entry/snapshot.go` (the new field may shift struct alignment).\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Write the failing store tests**\n\nAppend to `internal/store/store_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"Store history\", func() {\n\tIt(\"returns the op log and body versions\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"Tester\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\tid, err := s.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"T\", \"first\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(s.Update(id, \"second\", \"\")).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tlog, err := s.Log(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(len(log)).To(BeNumerically(\"\u003e=\", 2)) // create + at least one set-body\n\n\t\tvs, err := s.BodyVersions(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(vs[len(vs)-1].Body).To(Equal(\"second\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"reports Merged=false for a linear entry\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"Tester\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\tid, err := s.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"T\", \"b\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tmerged, err := s.Merged(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(merged).To(BeFalse())\n\t})\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Store Merged on real divergence\", func() {\n\tIt(\"reports Merged=true after concurrent edits sync into a merge commit\", func() {\n\t\tdirA := gitRepo()\n\t\tdirB := gitRepo()\n\t\ta, err := Init(dirA, \"A\", \"a@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = a.Close() })\n\t\tb, err := Init(dirB, \"B\", \"b@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = b.Close() })\n\t\tExpect(a.SetRemote(entry.TierShared, \"peer\", dirB)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(b.SetRemote(entry.TierShared, \"peer\", dirA)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\t// Common ancestor: A creates and both sync.\n\t\tid, err := a.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"T\", \"base\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(a.Push(entry.TierShared)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(b.Pull(entry.TierShared)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\t// Concurrent edits from the common base.\n\t\tExpect(a.Update(id, \"edit-from-A\", \"\")).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(b.Update(id, \"edit-from-B\", \"\")).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\t// A publishes; B pulls → B forms a merge commit joining both branches.\n\t\tExpect(a.Push(entry.TierShared)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(b.Pull(entry.TierShared)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tmerged, err := b.Merged(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(merged).To(BeTrue())\n\n\t\t// Both bodies survive in B's history (keep-both).\n\t\tvs, err := b.BodyVersions(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tbodies := make([]string, 0, len(vs))\n\t\tfor _, v := range vs {\n\t\t\tbodies = append(bodies, v.Body)\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(bodies).To(ContainElement(\"edit-from-A\"))\n\t\tExpect(bodies).To(ContainElement(\"edit-from-B\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n\u003e `SetRemote`, `Push`, `Pull`, `Update`, `Add` are existing store methods (see the sync tests). If `SetRemote`'s signature differs, match the existing sync test's usage.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run the store tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/store/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: FAIL — `s.Log` / `s.BodyVersions` / `s.Merged` undefined.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Implement the store methods**\n\nAdd to `internal/store/store.go`:\n\n```go\n// Log returns the operation history of an entry, searching all tiers.\nfunc (s *Store) Log(id entity.Id) ([]entry.LogEntry, error) {\n\tfor _, t := range entry.AllTiers() {\n\t\te, err := entry.Read(s.repo, t, id)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tif entity.IsErrNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"read %s in tier %s: %w\", id, t, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn e.Log(), nil\n\t}\n\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"entry %s not found\", id)\n}\n\n// BodyVersions returns each historical body of an entry, searching all tiers.\nfunc (s *Store) BodyVersions(id entity.Id) ([]entry.BodyVersion, error) {\n\tfor _, t := range entry.AllTiers() {\n\t\te, err := entry.Read(s.repo, t, id)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tif entity.IsErrNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"read %s in tier %s: %w\", id, t, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn e.BodyVersions(), nil\n\t}\n\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"entry %s not found\", id)\n}\n\n// Merged reports whether an entry's ref history contains a merge commit — a\n// coarse but honest signal that the entry was edited concurrently and synced.\nfunc (s *Store) Merged(id entity.Id) (bool, error) {\n\tfor _, t := range entry.AllTiers() {\n\t\tref := \"refs/\" + t.Namespace() + \"/\" + id.String()\n\t\thashes, err := s.repo.ListCommits(ref)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue // not in this tier\n\t\t}\n\t\tfor _, h := range hashes {\n\t\t\tc, err := s.repo.ReadCommit(h)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn false, fmt.Errorf(\"read commit %s: %w\", h, err)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif len(c.Parents) \u003e 1 {\n\t\t\t\treturn true, nil\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn false, nil\n\t}\n\treturn false, fmt.Errorf(\"entry %s not found\", id)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run the store tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/store/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: PASS (including the real-divergence merge test). Run `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go vet ./internal/store/`.\n\n\u003e If the divergence test fails because `Merged` returns false, check that `ListCommits` returns the full commit history (not just the head) and that `ReadCommit().Parents` is populated — both are guaranteed by the `repository` interface. If it fails on a sync error, align the remote/push/pull calls with the existing `kref sync CLI` test.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: gofmt + commit**\n\n```bash\ngofmt -w internal/store/store.go internal/store/store_test.go internal/entry/snapshot.go\ngit add internal/store/store.go internal/store/store_test.go internal/entry/snapshot.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(store): Log, BodyVersions, and Merged (commit-graph divergence signal)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: Render the log, body versions, and `◆ merged` marker\n\n**Files:** `internal/render/render.go`, `internal/render/render_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing render tests**\n\nAppend to `internal/render/render_test.go`:\n\n```go\nimport \"time\" // add to the import block if not present\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Log rendering\", func() {\n\tIt(\"prints one line per op with time, op, author, detail\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.Log(\u0026b, []entry.LogEntry{\n\t\t\t{Op: \"set-body\", Author: \"alice\", Time: time.Unix(0, 0).UTC(), Detail: \"7 chars\"},\n\t\t})\n\t\tout := b.String()\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"set-body\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"alice\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"7 chars\"))\n\t})\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"BodyVersions rendering\", func() {\n\tIt(\"prints each version with an author/time header and the body\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.BodyVersions(\u0026b, []entry.BodyVersion{\n\t\t\t{Author: \"alice\", Time: time.Unix(0, 0).UTC(), Body: \"first\"},\n\t\t\t{Author: \"claude\", Time: time.Unix(0, 0).UTC(), Body: \"second\"},\n\t\t})\n\t\tout := b.String()\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"first\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"second\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"claude\"))\n\t})\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"merged marker\", func() {\n\tIt(\"shows a merged marker in show and list when set\", func() {\n\t\tvar sb, lb bytes.Buffer\n\t\ts := \u0026entry.Snapshot{ID: entity.Id(\"a\"), Tier: \"shared\", Status: \"open\", Title: \"T\", Merged: true}\n\t\trender.Show(\u0026sb, s, false)\n\t\tExpect(sb.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"◆ merged\"))\n\t\trender.List(\u0026lb, []*entry.Snapshot{s}, false)\n\t\tExpect(lb.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"◆ merged\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the render tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: FAIL — `render.Log` / `render.BodyVersions` undefined; no `◆ merged`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement the renderers + markers**\n\nIn `internal/render/render.go`, add `\"time\"` to the import block, and append:\n\n```go\n// Log renders an entry's operation timeline, one line per op.\nfunc Log(w io.Writer, entries []entry.LogEntry) {\n\tfor _, e := range entries {\n\t\tts := e.Time.Format(\"2006-01-02 15:04\")\n\t\tline := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s  %-12s %s\", ts, e.Op, e.Author)\n\t\tif e.Detail != \"\" {\n\t\t\tline += \"  \" + e.Detail\n\t\t}\n\t\tfmt.Fprintln(w, line)\n\t}\n}\n\n// BodyVersions renders each historical body under an author/time header, so a\n// superseded version can be read off and recovered.\nfunc BodyVersions(w io.Writer, versions []entry.BodyVersion) {\n\tfor i, v := range versions {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"=== version %d — %s @ %s ===\\n%s\\n\\n\",\n\t\t\ti+1, v.Author, v.Time.Format(\"2006-01-02 15:04\"), v.Body)\n\t}\n}\n```\n\nIn `List`, where the row title is assembled (after the labels suffix, before the row `Fprintf`), append a merged marker:\n\n```go\n\t\tif it.Merged {\n\t\t\ttitle += \"  ◆ merged\"\n\t\t}\n```\n\nIn `Show`, after the labels block and before the provenance loop (or before the body), add:\n\n```go\n\tif snap.Merged {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintln(w, \"◆ merged — concurrent edits; see `kref log`\")\n\t}\n```\n\n\u003e `time` is used by the new renderers; `entry` and `fmt`/`io` are already imported.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run the render tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -6`\nExpected: PASS. Run `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go vet ./internal/render/`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: gofmt + commit**\n\n```bash\ngofmt -w internal/render/render.go internal/render/render_test.go\ngit add internal/render/render.go internal/render/render_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(render): op log, body versions, and the merged marker\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: `kref log` and `kref diff` commands\n\n**Files:** `cmd/kref/commands.go`, `cmd/kref/main.go`, `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing CLI specs**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"log and diff\", func() {\n\tadd := func(dir string) string {\n\t\tGinkgoHelper()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--title\", \"H\", \"--body\", \"v1\", \"--json\")\n\t\tvar a struct {\n\t\t\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026a)).To(Succeed())\n\t\treturn a.ID\n\t}\n\tIt(\"kref log shows the operation timeline\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\tid := add(dir)\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"update\", id, \"--body\", \"v2\")\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"log\", id)\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"create\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"set-body\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"kref diff shows each body version\", 